<item>
            <title>[PAY-4087] Payments V2 - Persist ACH TokenId E2E</title>
                <link>https://wellfit.atlassian.net/browse/PAY-4087</link>
                <project id="10016" key="PAY">Payments</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;PaymentsV2&apos;s &lt;tt&gt;PaymentHandler.HandleAsync&lt;/tt&gt; calls ACH Token Vault twice on a debit &#8212; a lookup (&lt;tt&gt;GetTokenByIdAsync&lt;/tt&gt;) when the request carries a token, and a create (&lt;tt&gt;CreateTokenAsync&lt;/tt&gt;) after a Worldpay-approved raw-account debit. Both return a &lt;tt&gt;tokenId&lt;/tt&gt;, but it&apos;s only ever written into the synchronous &lt;tt&gt;CreatePaymentResponse.TokenId&lt;/tt&gt; returned to the caller. It&apos;s never persisted to PV2&apos;s &lt;tt&gt;PaymentRequests&lt;/tt&gt; table, never included on &lt;tt&gt;PaymentDebitSubmittedEvent&lt;/tt&gt;, and the legacy-sync consumer (&lt;tt&gt;PlatformSyncService.SyncChargeAsync&lt;/tt&gt;) never sets &lt;tt&gt;Charge.Token&lt;/tt&gt; when building the &lt;tt&gt;Payments.Payments&lt;/tt&gt; row for approved ACH debits. Net effect: the vault token id exists for one request/response cycle and is then unrecoverable from any persisted record.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Fix requires adding the token id to at least one of: &lt;tt&gt;PaymentRequest&lt;/tt&gt; (PV2 aggregate), &lt;tt&gt;PaymentDebitSubmittedEvent&lt;/tt&gt;, or the legacy sync DTO/&lt;tt&gt;Charge&lt;/tt&gt; mapping &#8212; whichever the team decides is the right home for it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Once this lands, &lt;tt&gt;Payments.Payments.Token&lt;/tt&gt; becomes populatable for ACH for the first time, which also unblocks the ACH Return/NOC test fixture&apos;s anchor logic (&lt;tt&gt;ach-return-noc-fixtures/inject-ach-noc.sql&lt;/tt&gt;), which currently can never find a real ACH payment with a non-null vault token to anchor against.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Found while investigating why that NOC fixture could never find a real anchor in Dev.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
